message: I will constantly remove Finnish absurdities about WWII - no matter sources. Everyone knows that the Finns lost the war and had to obey the Soviet demand to start war on Germany.
Who is Platonov, some kind of an authority on warfare? Tali-Ihantala wasn't a "separate battle, it was a continuation of Vyborg offensive, which was a Russian victory.
So, if further attacks failed (for now) - BUT the Finns asked for Peace just the folliwing month - it would be a Russian defeat???? Please, gevi me a break!
/* Background */  citation for this can be found after next sentence (Pravda article of July 2, 1944)
Russian's interrupted the battle by their own choice, exactly as pre-planned (I have quoted Vasilevsky).
/* Soviet Gen. Platonov:  "repeated offensive attempts of the Soviet forces failed ... Leningrad front failed to carry out the tasks" */
see Russian Wikipedia article - the battle is called a Soviet victory. A victory is it when an attacking side capures cities like Vyborg and Petrozavodsk.
the same to you - look for the discussion on your own page (for instance read Churchill on Teheran 1943 - no plans of "conquering Finland"). Stop dreaming.
